Title: Svelte conventions

Summary: Keep Svelte views declarative and free of side-effects and styles.

Rules:
- No `<style>` blocks in `.svelte` files.
- No inline `style` attributes; use classes and SCSS.
- Explicitly subscribe/unsubscribe Svelte stores in views as per codebase pattern.
- Do not import Node/Electron in Svelte; use preload APIs via services.

